  427   /*
  428    *   This function updates active task flag for each subrate
  429    * and rate transition flags for tasks that exchange data.
  430    * The function assumes rate-monotonic multitasking scheduler.
  431    * The function must be called at model base rate so that
  432    * the generated code self-manages all its subrates and rate
  433    * transition flags.
  434    */

  436   {
  437     /* To ensure a deterministic data transfer between two rates,
  438      * data is transferred at the priority of a fast task and the frequency
  439      * of the slow task.  The following flags indicate when the data transfer
  440      * happens.  That is, a rate interaction flag is set true when both rates
  441      * will run, and false otherwise.
  442      */

  444     /* tid 1 shares data with slower tid rate: 7 */
  445     if (FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[1] == 0) {
  446       FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.RateInteraction.TID1_7 =
  447         (FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[7] == 0);
  448     }
  449   
  450     /* tid 3 shares data with slower tid rate: 7 */
  451     if (FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[3] == 0) {
  452       FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.RateInteraction.TID3_7 =
  453         (FSAC2021_V1_Running_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[7] == 0);

  554   real32_T rt_roundf_snf(real32_T u)
  555   {
  556     real32_T y;
  557     if ((real32_T)fabs(u) < 8.388608E+6F) {
  558       if (u >= 0.5F) {
  559         y = (real32_T)floor(u + 0.5F);
  560       } else if (u > -0.5F) {
  561         y = u * 0.0F;
  562       } else {
  563         y = (real32_T)ceil(u - 0.5F);
  564       }
  565     } else {
  566       y = u;
  567     }
  568   
  569     return y;
  570   }

 1830   real_T rt_roundd_snf(real_T u)
 1831   {
 1832     real_T y;
 1833     if (fabs(u) < 4.503599627370496E+15) {
 1834       if (u >= 0.5) {
 1835         y = floor(u + 0.5);
 1836       } else if (u > -0.5) {
 1837         y = u * 0.0;
 1838       } else {
 1839         y = ceil(u - 0.5);
 1840       }
 1841     } else {
 1842       y = u;
 1843     }
 1844   
 1845     return y;
 1846   }
